Burnley and West Brom are two of the most successful teams in the English Premier League. They have both been in the Premier League for over 20 years and have won a total of 54 league titles between them. Burnley have been champions twice, in 2004 and 2009, while West Brom have won the title once, in 2010. Burnley and West Brom are evenly matched, with each team having won a total of 52 league games. The key to their success has been their resilience in the face of difficult opposition.